  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypothesis: Group cycling classes (Spinning速) will improve pain and functional outcomes in
      patients with knee osteoarthritis

      Methods: Patients with symptomatic knee OA will be randomized to active Spinning速 classes 2-3
      per week or control group for 3 months. Outcomes including gait speed, WOMAC, KOOS, KOS, and
      VAS pain at rest and after 6 min walk will be performed at baseline and at 12 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
